quran[33]{c,v,t}:
  43,24,"He said, “What, even if I brought you better guidance than that which you found your fathers following?” They said, “For us, we deny that you are sent on a mission at all.”"
  43,25,So We took retribution from them. Now see what the end of those who rejected it was
  43,26,"Behold, Abraham said to his father and his people, “I indeed clear myself of what you worship"
  43,27,"“I worship only Him Who made me, and He will certainly guide me.”"
  43,28,"And he left it as a word to endure among those who came after him, that they might return"
  43,29,"Yes, I have given the good things of this life to these people and their parents, until the truth has come to them, and a messenger making things clear"
  43,30,"But when the truth came to them they said, “This is deception, and we reject it.”"
  43,31,"They also say, “Why is this Quran not sent down to some great person in either of the two cities?”"
  43,32,"Do they distribute the mercy of your Lord? It is We Who distribute among them their livelihood in the life of the present, and We raise some of them above others in ranks, so that some may benefit from the work of others, but the mercy of your Lord is better than that which they amass"
  43,33,"And were it not that all people might become one community, We would provide for everyone who rejects the Merciful Benefactor, silver roofs for their houses and silver stairways on which to climb"
  43,34,"And silver doors to their houses, and thrones of silver on which they could recline"
  43,35,"And adornments of gold. But all this is nothing but conveniences of the present life. The hereafter, in the sight of your Lord, is for the righteous"
  43,36,"If anyone turns himself from remembrance of God, the Merciful Benefactor, We appoint for him a devil to be a close friend to him"
  43,37,"They hinder them from the path, but they think that they are being guided aright"
  43,38,"Then, when such a one comes to Us, he says to his friend, “I wish that between you and me were the distance of East and West.” How terrible this friend is"
  43,39,"When you have done wrong, it will not benefit you that day, you will be partners in punishment"
  43,40,"Can you then make the deaf to hear, or give direction to the blind, or to those who wander in manifest error"
  43,41,"Even if We take you away, We will be sure to exact retribution from them"
  43,42,"Or We will show you that which We have promised them, for indeed We will prevail over them"
  43,43,"So hold fast to the revelation sent down to you, indeed you are on a straight way"
  43,44,"The Quran is indeed the message for you and for your people, and soon will you be brought to account"
  43,45,"And question those to whom we sent our messengers before you, did We appoint any deities other than God, the Merciful Benefactor, to be worshipped"
  43,46,"We sent Moses with Our signs to Pharaoh and his advisors. He said, “I am a messenger of the Lord of all worlds.”"
  43,47,"But when he came to them with Our signs, behold, they ridiculed them"
  43,48,"We showed them sign after sign, each greater than the other, and We seized them with punishment, in order that they might turn to Us"
  43,49,"And they said, “O sorcerer, invoke your Lord for us according to His covenant with you, for we will truly accept guidance.”"
  43,50,"But when We removed the penalty from them behold, they broke their word"
  43,51,"And Pharaoh proclaimed among his people saying, “O my people, does not the control of Egypt belong to me? See these streams flowing underneath me? What, do you not see"
  43,52,“Am I not better than this one who is seemingly insignificant and can hardly express himself clearly
  43,53,"“Then why are not gold bracelets bestowed on him, or why do there not come with him angels accompanying him?”"
  43,54,"So he made fools of his people, and they followed him. Truly were they a rebellious people"
  43,55,"So when they provoked Us, We took retribution from them, and We drowned them all"
  43,56,And We made them a people of history and an example in the hereafter